-- European shares hit 13-month low on growth concerns
-- By Atul Prakash
-- Thu Oct 16, 2014 05:56AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Oct 16 (Reuters) - Europe's benchmark FTSEurofirst 300 index <.FTEU3> slipped further to set a 13-month low on Wednesday on mounting worries over the strength of the global economy and concerns about deflation in the euro zone.

At 0949 GMT, the pan-European stock index was down 2.5 percent at 1,220.56 points after falling to a low of 1,215.62, its worst level since early September last year. The index has fallen more than 13 percent since mid-September of 2014. Britain's FTSE 100 index <.FTSE>, Germany's DAX <.GDAXI>, France's CAC <.FCHI> and Italy's FTSE MIB <.FTMIB> fell 1.5 to 3.3 percent.